##Unseal

WECHAT denganqing1984

Features, here, I will share my writing, reading the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I got up early in the morning. The first thing I did downstairs was go to the front wing. My father just got up and when I came in, he grinned and said, "son, how early are you getting up? " I put out my hand and said, "Give me the medicine box you want to buy, and I'll take a picture. " My father understood, immediately open the bedside table, take out a few medicine boxes to me.

I brought it to the hall, took pictures by the morning light, and sent them to my cousin. In addition, as my father instructed, list items to buy: "Four boxes of compound Ranitidine capsules, one box of Novartis needles, three boxes of glipizide tablets, four boxes of protamine biosynthetic human insulin injection, five bottles of Ranitidine Hydrochloride capsules. "

Mother came through the back door with a handful of fresh lettuce from the garden. She poked her head out and asked, "what are you doing? " I said, "I'm out of my medicine. I ran out of the insulin shot. I couldn't get a new one in town, so I asked my cousin if I could. He's on the street. It's easy to get there and back. "

The mother glared at the Father: "You AH, while your son in the house, a day to the black let people spend money! " The father held the medicine box handed over to the mother to see: "These drugs are not expensive, and really run out... " the mother continued to stare at him: "The past said! "! You want your son to buy you sugar-free milk, you want your son to buy you this medicine, that medicine..."

Seeing my father's face embarrassed, I got up and pushed my mother to the kitchen. "Mom, it's OK. It doesn't cost much. Don't tell me. " My mother was helpless, he looked at me and said, "you spoil him too much. He is just like a little boy. The more you spoil him, the more he wants to find you. " He glared at his father again and turned to the kitchen.
We returned to the hall and sat down. My cousin returned to Wechat and asked, "do you really need to buy so many boxes? They will be unsealed in a few days. By March 15 or so, you will probably be able to come to the street. If you buy medicine now, the price at the drugstore will start to rise, and it will be much more expensive. "

Then he asked me to ask my father if the medicine would last until the 15th or so. As soon as my father heard this, he quickly said, "Don't bother him! I have enough medicine. We'll go home then. " He told my cousin what my father had said, cousin said good, "wait until the 15th or so to see, if that time has not been opened, I go to the pharmacy to look. " Father picked up the medicine box and put it into the bedside table, "then we wait and see. "
At breakfast, through the window, I heard the people on the embankment say that the dike van had withdrawn to the side. I ran to the balcony to see, block the car really did not have, usually wearing red armband duty village cadres did not see people. I also thought of the POLDER Wechat Group sent "Wuxue co-ordinated promotion of Epidemic Prevention and control and orderly resumption of production and resumption of work" document, it seems to be slowly loose.

On the lonely dike road, people gradually increased, and everyone's face showed an excited look. They get together, someone said in a loud voice, "I saw the shovel. I think I'll go to another embankment and shovel the mound that is blocking the road. ". MORE CARS ON THE ROAD!"another nodded his head and said,"Oh, and then shut down, people are going crazy! Every day after eating sleepy, sleepy eat, sit eat mountain empty, people have gained more than ten pounds, gIGGLE.

I went back to my room and started working online. At home, though, there is no less work to be done than in Beijing. Busy to noon, physical weakness, eyelids heavy, the spirit of the head is very poor, see to deal with the document, can not calm down, the forehead began to some fever, I wonder if the fever.

At lunch, talk to your parents about your health. They looked at me with concern, and my mother said, "it's a cold again. It's hot and cold. " My father said, "you drink plenty of boiled water! " After dinner, I went upstairs to continue my work and drank as much hot water as I could. By two o'clock in the afternoon, much better, no fever symptoms, no sneezing, coughing, it seems as before, come quickly, go quickly. I'm relieved, too.
The screeching of tires against the road poured out of the window. It had been a long time since I had heard such a noise. Except for delivery and garbage trucks, the road was quiet. Dust was thrown up and sprinkled on the rape flowers by the road.

A dozen people gathered next door, and a man at their door was grilling chicken wings, eggplant, and potatoes on a barbecue, the familiar smell of cumin wafting over his face. How I'VE MISSED YOU! It's been a long, long time since I smelled anything like that. I miss the smell of fast food, the smell of hot and sour powder, and the smell of all kinds of junk food.

Already calm heart, jump up, lively up, nose, arms, eyes, heels, want to move, want to touch the outside world. A world that used to be so ordinary is now so precious.
Thinking, father came into my room, "still burning? " I said. "already done. " He let out a sigh of relief. "Good! Good! I went to the drugstore. I didn't get cold medicine. They say if you have a fever, you have to go to the hospital,"I asked in surprise."You went to the street

He said yes. Seeing that the barricades were gone, my father drove the three-wheeler to the city on his own, and was able to get through the checkpoints without a permit from the village council or a pass. The drug store was open, there was a long line, and people began to fill the streets.

I said to my father, "you should have asked me to go with you. " My father said, "you have work to do, so I'll go home. " He stood in my room for a while, then looked at the window for a while, then turned away, he gave another order: "remember to drink water, Know Bo? Do not catch a cold, otherwise this time good trouble. " I said yes. Then he walked slowly out the door and down the stairs.
After dinner, my mother said, "Qinger, let's go for a walk on the LEVEE. " I quickly said yes and changed my shoes. Walking slowly along the embankment of the Yangtze River, all the way to see is like a return to the old Chinese New Year scene.

Every door was open, cars parked, this pile, that pile, are adults talking, children in the chase play, a lot of strange faces appeared. I said with emotion: "Good lively! " The mother said: "A way, go home, relatives, see friends, all come over. "

On the Bank of the Yangtze River, people walking in twos and threes often heard laughter. Standing on the dam with my mother, I looked back at the embankment, almost surrounded by rape flowers blooming in all directions, yellow, bright, floral blowing in the wind. Turning through the shelter, the lights sporadically lit up on the other side of the river. The water was vast and the ship moved silently in the middle of the water.

I had never seen such a beautiful home, or so much of it, at this time of year. I had never seen it. When I saw him this time, first joy came to my heart, then melancholy. It's unsealed. It's not far from when I go back to Beijing.
When it was dark, everyone got down from the embankment and walked slowly toward the dike. My mother said, "this is a once in a century! " My aunt pursed her lips and said, "I see, it is a once in a millennium. At this time, several generations of people in the dyke are all here. Do you think there will be any in the past? I don't think there will be any in the future! " Then they all laughed again. The aunt went on to say: "when the time comes, only the old man will be left in the dike again. " Everyone said yes, and each sighed and sighed.

Into the dyke, along the embankment, the more you go, the fewer people, we all go home. In the end, it was just me and my mother, because our house was at the back of the dike. The excitement was in their homes, and the road was quiet.

I took my mother's hand, my mother looked at me, asked: "Tomorrow to give you some tea eggs to eat, to get Bo? " I said with surprise: "I am not tomorrow. " Every time I leave home, my mother always boil more than a dozen tea eggs let me bring. I added, "I don't know how I'll be able to leave Hubei, even though the dike is now open. " My mother nodded. "I'll cook it later. "

After a while, the mother asked: "Do you still want to eat? " I smiled: "I have not so fast walk. " The mother smiled and did not speak. Soon, we'll be walking home.

The rape flowers spread far and wide
